  'Lifestyle'
),
(
  'Family Life in Calvia: Schools, Activities, and Community',
  'family-life-calvia',
  'Calvia offers families an enviable combination of outdoor lifestyle, international schooling, and a safe, welcoming community. Here is a comprehensive guide to raising children in southwest Mallorca.',
  E'Choosing to raise a family in Calvia is a decision that combines practical advantages with an extraordinary quality of life. The municipality invests heavily in family infrastructure, and the international community provides a diverse, welcoming environment for children of all ages.\n\n## International Schools\n\nCalvia and the surrounding area is served by several highly regarded international schools offering British, German, and International Baccalaureate curricula. Most schools operate from early years through to university preparation and maintain small class sizes that facilitate individualised attention. The bilingual environment means children naturally develop fluency in multiple languages.\n\n## After-School Activities\n\nThe range of extracurricular activities available in Calvia surpasses many larger cities. Water sports academies offer structured programmes in sailing, kayaking, and paddleboarding. Tennis and padel academies operate year-round. Dance, martial arts, and music schools cater to every interest. The year-round outdoor lifestyle means children spend significantly more time in physical activity than their peers in northern European climates.\n\n## Outdoor Adventures for Families\n\nCalvia''s coastline provides endless opportunities for family exploration. Gentle snorkelling at Cala Portals Vells reveals fish, octopus, and colourful sea life. The flat coastal paths between beaches are manageable for younger children. Inland, the foothills of the Tramuntana offer family-friendly hiking routes with picnic areas and natural springs.\n\n## Healthcare\n\nCalvia is well served by both public and private healthcare. Several international medical centres offer paediatric services with English, German, and Scandinavian-speaking staff. Emergency services are reliable and responsive. The area''s clean air and active outdoor lifestyle contribute to generally excellent child health outcomes.\n\n## The International Community\n\nCalvia''s large and established international community means families quickly find social networks through school, sports clubs, and community groups. Organised playdates, birthday parties, and social events create a connected childhood experience. The diversity of the community teaches children cultural openness from an early age.\n\n## Practical Considerations\n\nThe cost of schooling ranges widely depending on the institution and curriculum. Transportation to schools is typically provided by the schools themselves. The municipality maintains excellent playgrounds, sports facilities, and public spaces throughout the area. Summer holiday programmes offered by schools, sports clubs, and the municipality itself ensure children remain engaged during the long break.',
  'https://images.pexels.com/photos/1683975/pexels-photo-1683975.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800',
  'Calvia Editorial',
  '2025-12-28T10:00:00Z',
